# Availability Open/Close Indicator & Portfolio Name Overlay Implementation Plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Replace hardcoded time ranges with Open/Closed status dots in the availability section, and always show the portfolio item name overlay on 360 portfolio cards regardless of thumbnail availability.

**Architecture:** Two independent, display-only edits in two separate component files. No API, store, or type changes required. Each task is self-contained and can be committed independently.

**Tech Stack:** Next.js 14, React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS

## Global Constraints

- Do not modify any API layer, Zustand stores, or type definitions
- Do not change the photographer card component (`src/components/photographer-card.tsx`)
- Tailwind classes only — no inline styles
- The existing `row.c` boolean (true = closed) is the sole source of truth for open/closed state

---

### Task 1: Service Hours — Replace Time Text with Open/Closed Dot Indicator

**Files:**
- Modify: `src/components/photographer-profile.tsx:89–102` (hours data) and `src/components/photographer-profile.tsx:276–278` (hours render)

**Interfaces:**
- Consumes: `hours` array with shape `{ d: string; h: string; c: boolean }[]` — `c` is `true` when closed
- Produces: same array shape, `h` value is now `"Open"` or `"Closed"` (no time strings)

---

- [ ] **Step 1: Update the hours data — dynamic branch**

In `src/components/photographer-profile.tsx`, find line 93:

```ts
h: availableDays.has(d) ? "09:00 – 18:00" : "Closed",
```

Change to:

```ts
h: availableDays.has(d) ? "Open" : "Closed",
```

- [ ] **Step 2: Update the hours data — static fallback branch**

In the same file, lines 97–102 currently read:

```ts
{ d: "Sunday",    h: "Closed",       c: true  },
{ d: "Monday",    h: "09:00 – 18:00", c: false },
{ d: "Tuesday",   h: "09:00 – 18:00", c: false },
{ d: "Wednesday", h: "09:00 – 18:00", c: false },
{ d: "Thursday",  h: "09:00 – 18:00", c: false },
{ d: "Friday",    h: "09:00 – 17:00", c: false },
```

Replace with:

```ts
{ d: "Sunday",    h: "Closed", c: true  },
{ d: "Monday",    h: "Open",   c: false },
{ d: "Tuesday",   h: "Open",   c: false },
{ d: "Wednesday", h: "Open",   c: false },
{ d: "Thursday",  h: "Open",   c: false },
{ d: "Friday",    h: "Open",   c: false },
```

- [ ] **Step 3: Update the render — add colored dot before status text**

In the same file, lines 276–278 currently read:

```tsx
<span className={`font-mono text-xs ${row.c ? "text-muted-foreground/60" : ""}`}>
  {row.h}
</span>
```

Replace with:

```tsx
<span className="flex items-center gap-1.5">
  <span
    className={`inline-block size-1.5 rounded-full ${
      row.c ? "bg-muted-foreground/40" : "bg-green-500"
    }`}
  />
  <span className={`font-mono text-xs ${row.c ? "text-muted-foreground/60" : ""}`}>
    {row.h}
  </span>
</span>
```

- [ ] **Step 4: Verify visually**

Run the dev server:

```bash
npm run dev
```

Navigate to any photographer detail page (e.g. `/photographer/<slug>`). In the "Availability / Service hours" section verify:
- Each open day shows a small green dot followed by `"Open"`
- Closed days show a muted gray dot followed by `"Closed"` in muted color
- No time strings (`"09:00"`, `"18:00"`, `"17:00"`) appear anywhere in the hours list

- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**

```bash
git add src/components/photographer-profile.tsx
git commit -m "feat: replace service hours time text with open/closed dot indicator"
```

