### Task 2: Portfolio Thumbnail — Always Show Name Overlay

**Files:**
- Modify: `src/components/pages/photographer/photographerPortfolio.tsx:65` (add `relative`) and after line `80` (insert name overlay)

**Interfaces:**
- Consumes: `item.businessName`, `item.title` — both optional strings, already null-coalesced in the existing thumbnail branch
- Produces: name overlay rendered in both thumbnail-present and thumbnail-absent states

---

- [ ] **Step 1: Add `relative` positioning to the placeholder wrapper**

In `src/components/pages/photographer/photographerPortfolio.tsx`, line 65 currently reads:

```tsx
<div className="flex h-[128px] w-full flex-col items-center justify-center gap-1.5 rounded-md border border-dashed bg-muted/40">
```

Change to:

```tsx
<div className="relative flex h-[128px] w-full flex-col items-center justify-center gap-1.5 rounded-md border border-dashed bg-muted/40">
```

- [ ] **Step 2: Insert name overlay after the "No preview" span**

After line 80 (the `"No preview"` span) and before the closing `</div>` of the placeholder, insert:

```tsx
{(item.businessName ?? item.title) && (
  <div className="absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 rounded-b-md bg-linear-to-t from-black via-black/70 to-transparent p-2">
    <span className="block w-full truncate text-sm text-white">
      {item.businessName ?? item.title}
    </span>
  </div>
)}
```

After this change, the full no-thumbnail branch should look like:

```tsx
<div className="relative flex h-[128px] w-full flex-col items-center justify-center gap-1.5 rounded-md border border-dashed bg-muted/40">
  <svg
    viewBox="0 0 48 48"
    width="40"
    height="40"
    fill="none"
    aria-hidden="true"
    className="text-muted-foreground/40"
  >
    <circle cx="24" cy="24" r="21" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth="1.5" strokeDasharray="3 2" />
    <rect x="11" y="17" width="26" height="18" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth="1.5" />
    <path d="M20 17v-3h8v3" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth="1.5" strokeLinecap="round" strokeLinejoin="round" />
    <circle cx="24" cy="26" r="5" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth="1.5" />
    <circle cx="24" cy="26" r="1.5" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.5" />
  </svg>
  <span className="font-mono text-[9px] uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground/40">No preview</span>
  {(item.businessName ?? item.title) && (
    <div className="absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 rounded-b-md bg-linear-to-t from-black via-black/70 to-transparent p-2">
      <span className="block w-full truncate text-sm text-white">
        {item.businessName ?? item.title}
      </span>
    </div>
  )}
</div>
```

- [ ] **Step 3: Verify visually**

With the dev server still running, navigate to a photographer detail page that has 360 portfolio items. Switch between portfolio tabs (GoThru, Google, Panorra, Matterport). Verify:
- Cards **with** a valid thumbnail: name overlay at bottom unchanged ✓
- Cards **without** a thumbnail (dashed border + camera icon + "No preview"): name now appears at the bottom in the gradient overlay
- If an item has neither `businessName` nor `title`, no overlay appears (no empty gradient bar)

- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**

```bash
git add src/components/pages/photographer/photographerPortfolio.tsx
git commit -m "feat: always show portfolio item name overlay regardless of thumbnail availability"
```

---

## Acceptance Criteria

### Feature 1 — Service Hours Open/Closed Indicator

- **AC1:** The "Availability / Service hours" section never displays any time string (`09:00`, `18:00`, `17:00`, or any `HH:MM` format).
- **AC2:** Every available day renders a green dot (`bg-green-500`) followed by the text `"Open"` in normal foreground color.
- **AC3:** Every unavailable day renders a muted gray dot (`bg-muted-foreground/40`) followed by the text `"Closed"` in muted color (`text-muted-foreground/60`).
- **AC4:** Both code paths produce the correct output — photographers who have availability data from the API, and those who fall back to the static default list.

### Feature 2 — Portfolio Thumbnail Name Overlay

- **AC1:** Portfolio items with a valid thumbnail continue to show the gradient name overlay at the bottom, unchanged.
- **AC2:** Portfolio items with no thumbnail (dashed border + camera icon + "No preview") also show the gradient name overlay at the bottom of the card.
- **AC3:** If an item has neither `businessName` nor `title`, no empty gradient bar is rendered.
- **AC4:** The behavior is consistent across all four portfolio types: GoThru, Google Street View, Panorra, and Matterport.
